Collect list of capacity reservation target from all queues/compute-resources in the fleet config.

Fleet config json has the following format:
{
    "my-queue": {
        "my-compute-resource": {
           "Api": "create-fleet",
            "CapacityType": "on-demand|spot|capacity-block",
            "AllocationStrategy": "lowest-price|capacity-optimized",
            "Instances": [
                { "InstanceType": "p4d.24xlarge" }
            ],
            "MaxPrice": "",
            "Networking": {
                "SubnetIds": ["subnet-123456"]
            },
            "CapacityReservationId": "id"
        }
    }
}

Parse out which launch configurations (queue/compute resource) are requested by slurm nodes from NodeName.

Valid NodeName format: {queue_name}-{st/dy}-{compute_resource_name}-{number}
Sample NodeName: queue1-st-computeres1-2
